    "created_at": "2018-04-13T16:32:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-04-13T16:32:27Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So, what I am getting at is that by doing something one way in node, and another way in tests, we're putting ourselves in a situation where we're not testing what actually happens in reality. What I am inferring from your last response is that if doing this unref can cause memory leaks in tests, doing it in the node codepath only might cause memory leaks in node that will then go undetected because we're not doing it when testing for memory leaks.\r\n\r\nMoreover, I am also getting the feeling that this is caused by the global pollset shutdown change, indicating that the rootcause of this is in fact in there, and that it wasn't the right thing to do to begin with. This is where the fix needs to happen, not with this workaround.\r\n\r\nOr to be more blunt, you can't keep adding kludges to fix other kludges."
  },
