    "updated_at": "2018-04-13T17:17:49Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So my short answer here is \"no\". There are lots of changes in grpc/grpc-node that our users are waiting for, and some of our future release schedule depend on features being released now.\r\n\r\nNow, I am going to suggest something potentially controversial, but since grpc/grpc-node is its own separate repository, grpc-node could still be released for version 1.11, but with the grpc-core submodule being pointed at 1.10. This might create the possibility that some of the grpc-node users will be puzzled as to why some grpc-core bugfixes in 1.11 aren't present in grpc-node 1.11, but this would allow us to move forward nonetheless."
